## Quick install & execution

- Briefly

```
$ wget https://s3.amazonaws.com/blazemeter-images/bzm-app/install/docker/install.run \
&& chmod +x install.run \
&& ./install.run
 ...
$ docker logs -f $(/usr/local/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/bzm-data-router)
```

## Installation

- Launcher
```
/usr/local/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/bzm-data-router
```
- SSL certs
```
/etc/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/certs/*
```
- Config
```
/etc/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/.env
```

- Installer [source](https://github.com/Blazemeter/private-cloud/blob/master/install/docker/install.sh) + [makeself](https://makeself.io) = [install.run](https://s3.amazonaws.com/blazemeter-images/bzm-app/install/docker/install.run)
- More in [wiki](https://blazemeter.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RD/pages/736919787/Private+Cloud+Docker+installer+WAP-14064)


## Configuration & execution


- Environment variables exposed to Docker
    ```
    # reconfigure
    vim /etc/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/.env
    docker rm -f bzm-data-router \
    && docker logs -f $(/usr/local/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/bzm-data-router)
    ```

    - How it uses `/etc/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/.env`?
    ```
    # how config is used
    docker run ... --env-file "/etc/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/.env" ...
    ```

    - Restart
    ```
    # restart
    $ docker logs -f $(/usr/local/blazemeter/PrivateCloud/bzm-data-router)
    ```
